====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[go]]; to [[proceed]] (to a [[place]])
#* {{zh-x|大夫 七十 而 致事。若 不得 謝，則 必 賜 之 几 杖，行役 以 婦人。適 四方，乘 安車{jū}。|A great officer, when he is seventy, should resign (his charge of) affairs. If he were not allowed to resign, there must be given him a stool and staff. When travelling on service, he must have the attendance of his wife. When '''going to''' any other state, he will ride in an easy carriage.|ref=Liji}}
#* {{zh-x|三 人 行 而 一 人 惑，所 適 者 猶 可 致 也，惑 者 少{shǎo} 也；二 人 惑 則 勞 而 不 至，惑 者 勝 也。|If three men were walking together, and (only) one of them be under a delusion (as to their way), they may yet reach their goal [i.e. place they are '''going to'''], the deluded being the minority; but if two of them were under the delusion, they will not succeed, the deluded being the majority.|ref=Zhuangzi}}
